Hey @chrcoe 

I think this can be done via normal logging filters. You can use `threadlocal` while setting up the filters. 


    class ContextFilter(logging.Filter):
        def __init__(self):
            super(ContextFilter, self).__init__()
            self.thread_local = threading.local()
    
        def set_version(self, version):
            self.thread_local.version = version
    
        def filter(self, record):
            try:
                record.version = self.thread_local.version
            except AttributeError:
                record.version = "1.0"
            return True

Let me know if this suits your requirement. I am closing this issue for now.

