Adding corresponding `cancel()` calls in `TelegramBaseClient.disconnect()` seems to be sufficient, though I don't know if there's other state that needs any clearing up.

```python
def disconnect(self):
    """Disconnects from the Telegram server"""
    ...
    if self._recv_loop:
        self._recv_loop.cancel()
    if self._ping_loop:
        self._ping_loop.cancel()
    if self._state_loop:
        self._state_loop.cancel()
```

